import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lumosity', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Lumosity: {:.2f}'.format(data['lumosity'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['color'])
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    color_counts_df = pd.DataFrame({'color': color_counts.index, 'count': color_counts.values})
    chart = sns.barplot(x='color', y='count', data=color_counts_df)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the most common color in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['saturation', 'count']]
    sns.scatterplot(x='saturation', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between saturation and count?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.astype({'key': 'category'})
    chart = sns.countplot(x='key', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of key values?', wrap=True)
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
